"There are many stories about the Great Bog and the Forest of Life; the "
"mysterious flow of magic, the hostile environment, and the beasts and "
"monsters that call that place home. Numerous tales from adventures that "
"return from that accursed place, tales about terrifying swamp men covered in "
"foliage. Snaring the unfortunate adventurer, dragging them into the murky "
"waters or being hoisted into the canopy. Then attacking from all around be "
"it from rising from the watery ground or descending from the tress, sowing "
"fear and panic in the most stewarded person. These despicable creatures are "
"not men but a specialized salamander, Swamp Salamanders. Unlike their Green "
"Salamander comrades that cover their bodies in foliage to help conceal "
"themselves, Swamp Salamanders purposely root living foliage into their body "
"giving them freakish camouflage that confuses and fools the most keen eyed "
"foes. Even other Swamp Salamanders have difficulty spotting their own "
"brethren."
msgstr ""

